Titulo: Electrochemical performance of LSCF-based composite cathodes for intermediate temperature SOFCs

Sentencas: La0.6Sr0.4C0.2Fe0.8O2-delta, (LSCF), LSCF-(Gd0.2Ce0.8O3) GDC, LSCF-platinum (Pt) and LSCF-GDC-Pt, were fabricated for the purpose of investigating their potential use in intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells (IT-SOFCs) and the relationship between the electrocatalytic characteristics and electrode microstructure of the electrochemical cells.
Titulo: Electrochemical performance of LSCF-based composite cathodes for intermediate temperature SOFCs

Sentencas: Both the LSCF-GDC and LSCF-Pt composite electrodes seemed to perform better than the LSCF electrode for oxygen reduction.
Titulo: Electrochemical performance of LSCF-based composite cathodes for intermediate temperature SOFCs

Sentencas: The polarization resistance was significantly reduced in the case of the composite electrodes.
Titulo: Electrochemical performance of LSCF-based composite cathodes for intermediate temperature SOFCs

Sentencas: The incorporation of Pt particles in the LSCF electrode was found to be effective over the entire temperature range for which measurements were taken.
Titulo: Electrochemical performance of LSCF-based composite cathodes for intermediate temperature SOFCs

Sentencas: Adding the GDC resulted in microstructural changes taking place in the LSCF electrode, and a low polarization resistance was obtained at temperatures of 600 degrees C and lower.
Titulo: Electrochemical performance of LSCF-based composite cathodes for intermediate temperature SOFCs

Sentencas: Based on the impedance spectrum data, it was considered that Pt might accelerate the oxygen adsorption at high temperature.
Titulo: Electrochemical performance of LSCF-based composite cathodes for intermediate temperature SOFCs

Sentencas: On the other hand, GDC seemed to serve as a fast oxygen ion diffusion path at lower temperatures.
